<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-12-31T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-01-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="283" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                            </head>
                            <p>On March 17 <persName corresp="#p_CGLD1">Clay</persName> held a top
                                secret teletype conference with <persName corresp="#p_VTS1">Voorhees</persName> concerning the general trend of events in
                                Germany and the negotiation <pb facs="0610" n="573" xml:id="pg_573"/> in London on prohibited and restricted industries. For the
                                transcript of this conference, see <ref target="#pg_105">page
                                    105</ref>.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>